properties.areaDesc: North Snowy Range Foothills; South Laramie Range Foothills; South Laramie Range; Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County
properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 30 at 2:32PM MST until February 2 at 8:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...POTENTIAL FOR HIGH WINDS EXISTS FRIDAY THROUGH SUNDAY MORNING
FOR THE SOUTHEAST WYOMING WIND-PRONE AREAS...

* WHAT...West winds 30 to 40 MPH with gusts up to 65 MPH possible.

* WHERE...Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County, North
Snowy Range Foothills, South Laramie Range and South Laramie
Range Foothills.

* WHEN...From Friday morning through Sunday morning.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Potential blow off and blow
over risk for lightweight and high profile vehicles, including
camper trailers and semi trucks.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM FRIDAY MORNING THROUGH SUNDAY MORNING
